default12.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe Building Regulations in place across the UK currently 
defaultdisincentivise designers to use high thermal mass solutions to reduce and regulate heating energy demand, and to use natural ventilation systems (as opposed to the mechanical ventilation used in the PassivHaus system).
default Whilst both approaches are valid
default 
defaultgrea
defaultter flexibility needs to be introduced to enable natural heating
default, cooling
default and ventilation solutions can compete with mechanical solutions, and without relaxing emissions reduction goals
default (e.g. see CIBSE, 2013
default; Roaf, 2012; &amp; Humphreys et al. 2011
default)
